# API and Service Layer Rules

## Layering

Route handlers:
- validate input
- call services
- map errors to HTTP responses

Services:
- contain domain logic
- enforce permissions
- coordinate repositories

Repositories:
- handle database calls only
- no business logic

## Permissions

All write operations must:

- require authentication
- enforce ownership where applicable

Ownership examples:
- image posts
- datasets
- artifacts

Never rely on UI-only protection.
